sif3.infra.common.env.types
Class EnvironmentInfo

java.lang.Object
  sif3.infra.common.env.types.EnvironmentInfo
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
ConsumerEnvironment, ProviderEnvironment
public class EnvironmentInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class is a super-class for environment management. It can be used for Consumer and Provider environment managemnt but it is unlikely to be used on its own. It holds base infromation that is required in either environment and must be maintained in either environment (Consumer, Provider).

Author:
Joerg Huber

getServices

public java.util.ArrayList<ServiceInfo> getServices()
List of services available for this environment. This are OBJECT, UTILITY and FUNCTIONal services. Each service also has an assigned zone and context with it, both of which can be ommited. If they are ommited then the default zone and context are assumed as per SIF3 specification.

See desc.
